WEBVTT

00:05.004 --> 00:07.048
♪ ♪

00:20.311 --> 00:22.856
♪ ♪

00:33.199 --> 00:36.786
(bell tolling in distance)

00:36.870 --> 00:39.247
(indistinct chatter)

00:52.844 --> 00:55.764
MS. WATSON:
This is why Wordsworth says

00:55.847 --> 00:59.809
that poetry is the spontaneous
overflow of powerful feelings.

00:59.893 --> 01:02.270
-(door creaks)
-The emotion is contemplated

01:02.353 --> 01:04.855
to the subject of--
Ah, there she is.

01:04.938 --> 01:08.234
This place can be a maze.
Class, this is Irene.

01:08.318 --> 01:11.696
She's gonna be joining us
for the rest of the semester.

01:12.864 --> 01:14.949
Go ahead, introduce yourself.

01:15.033 --> 01:17.327
Uh, hi, hello.

01:17.410 --> 01:19.913
Like she said, my name is Irene.

01:21.247 --> 01:22.665
MS. WATSON (chuckles):
And where you're from

01:22.749 --> 01:23.875
and what you like.

01:23.958 --> 01:25.960
Oh, um...

01:26.044 --> 01:28.046
I guess I like stuff.

01:28.129 --> 01:30.882
Um... Indian food

01:30.965 --> 01:33.802
-and memes and monsters.
-(retches)

01:33.885 --> 01:35.678
Cool stuff.

01:35.762 --> 01:38.681
I mean, I-I like other things,
too, you kn-- whatever.

01:38.765 --> 01:40.350
Irene will be starting
her science fair project

01:40.433 --> 01:41.976
tomorrow so she can catch up.

01:42.060 --> 01:43.812
And it's a spooky one.
(chuckles)

01:43.895 --> 01:45.480
Uh, tell the class.

01:45.563 --> 01:49.359
Um, I-I thought I might do
a project on psychic abilities?

01:49.442 --> 01:50.902
-Yuck.
-(girls snickering)

01:50.985 --> 01:51.986
IRENE:
Do psychic powers,

01:52.070 --> 01:53.822
like, do they really exist?

01:53.905 --> 01:55.824
MS. WATSON:
Ooh, we can't wait to find out.

01:55.907 --> 01:58.243
Irene, go ahead and have a seat.

01:58.326 --> 01:59.828
GWEN:
She looks like she's planning

01:59.911 --> 02:02.163
on being the first
girl school shooter.

02:02.247 --> 02:05.500
-(laughs)
-Jesus, Gwen. Funny, though.

02:05.583 --> 02:08.044
When we talk about the sublime,
what do we mean?

02:09.503 --> 02:12.173
(laughter)

02:12.257 --> 02:14.425
Take a look at the elements
of this poem.

02:14.509 --> 02:18.847
There are concepts and motions
that are heightened

02:18.930 --> 02:21.057
beyond typical human experience.

02:21.140 --> 02:25.854
That's what Wordsworth and Blake
and Hugo are grasping at here,

02:25.937 --> 02:28.022
the sublime.

02:28.106 --> 02:31.025
These poets also express
a clear interest

02:31.109 --> 02:35.113
in the deification
of imagination.

02:35.196 --> 02:39.117
Imagination is placed
above experience.

02:40.159 --> 02:41.870
(whispers):
Irene?

02:41.953 --> 02:44.914
Do you need a pencil
so you can answer the question?

02:44.998 --> 02:46.416
(laughter)

02:46.499 --> 02:50.086
MS. WATSON: Think of these poets
as expressing an ideal,

02:50.169 --> 02:54.215
instead of reflecting on the
nature of reality around them.

02:58.177 --> 03:00.138
(giggling)

03:00.221 --> 03:02.432
{\an5}MADISON:
Hey. Your head got in the way
of my pencil.

03:02.515 --> 03:04.976
Could you fetch it?

03:05.059 --> 03:07.896
Cupcake. My pencil.

03:07.979 --> 03:10.106
Now.

03:10.189 --> 03:11.900
NARRATOR:
High school.

03:11.983 --> 03:13.776
It's a period that,
for most of us,

03:13.860 --> 03:16.237
already feels
like a waking nightmare,

03:16.321 --> 03:18.489
one in which we're lost
in a maze,

03:18.573 --> 03:20.491
searching for ourselves.

03:20.575 --> 03:22.160
But what if,

03:22.243 --> 03:24.954
during this precarious phase
of our development,

03:25.038 --> 03:28.458
you introduced a set
of extraordinary powers?

03:28.541 --> 03:31.294
That's all it will take
to send the student body

03:31.377 --> 03:36.799
of St. Mary's Boarding School
on a harrowing field trip

03:36.883 --> 03:39.135
to The Twilight Zone.

03:39.761 --> 03:41.471
<i>(The Twilight Zone</i> theme
playing)

03:41.554 --> 03:43.139
<i>You're traveling</i>
<i>through another dimension,</i>

03:43.222 --> 03:46.809
<i>a dimension not only of</i>
<i>sight and sound but of mind.</i>

03:46.893 --> 03:50.021
<i>It is the middle ground</i>
<i>between light and shadow,</i>

03:50.104 --> 03:52.815
<i>between science</i>
<i>and superstition.</i>

03:52.899 --> 03:55.318
{\an8}<i>And it lies between</i>
<i>the pit of one's fears</i>

03:55.401 --> 03:58.154
{\an8}<i>and the summit</i>
<i>of one's knowledge.</i>

03:58.237 --> 04:01.324
<i>You are now traveling through</i>
<i>a dimension of imagination.</i>

04:01.407 --> 04:05.328
<i>You've just crossed over</i>
<i>into The Twilight Zone.</i>

04:12.377 --> 04:14.921
(girls laughing in distance)

04:23.388 --> 04:25.890
(bell tolling in distance)

04:30.436 --> 04:33.231
(indistinct chatter)

04:33.314 --> 04:36.067
(laughter)

04:37.986 --> 04:41.030
{\an5}<i>IRENE:</i>
<i>I think I would like</i>
<i>to change my project.</i>

04:41.114 --> 04:42.490
Oh?

04:42.573 --> 04:45.201
{\an8}Yeah, so I was
thinking about it,

04:45.284 --> 04:49.080
{\an8}and I'm not sure that psychic
stuff really represents me.

04:49.163 --> 04:50.999
{\an8}I'm sorry, sweetie,
but the science fair guides

04:51.082 --> 04:52.333
{\an8}have already been printed.

04:52.417 --> 04:55.420
{\an8}I'm sure everyone
is gonna like your...

04:55.503 --> 04:59.424
{\an8}psychic, uh, test thing.

05:00.633 --> 05:03.011
{\an8}So, um,
these are called Zener cards.

05:03.094 --> 05:05.388
{\an8}They have one of five symbols
on them.

05:05.471 --> 05:08.057
{\an8}So, I'm gonna pull a card
from the deck and stare at it,

05:08.141 --> 05:10.393
{\an8}and then you write down
what you think the card is

05:10.476 --> 05:13.229
{\an8}by trying to, like,
read my mind.

05:13.312 --> 05:15.148
{\an8}I do not want to be
inside her mind.

05:15.231 --> 05:17.233
{\an8}MS. WATSON:
Quiet.

05:21.029 --> 05:23.364
{\an8}♪ ♪

05:28.494 --> 05:31.122
{\an8}(indistinct chatter in distance)

05:56.314 --> 05:58.649
{\an8}♪ ♪

06:20.797 --> 06:23.299
{\an8}-(muffled chatter)
-(music playing in distance)

06:28.179 --> 06:29.639
{\an8}(knocks softly)

06:41.067 --> 06:42.777
{\an8}♪ ♪

06:42.860 --> 06:44.362
{\an8}What?

06:44.445 --> 06:47.365
{\an8}-(singsongy): It's Irene.
-(chuckling)

06:47.448 --> 06:50.201
{\an8}Hi. Uh, is this a bad time?

06:50.284 --> 06:51.536
{\an8}Always.

06:51.619 --> 06:53.454
{\an8}Oh. Well, uh,

06:53.538 --> 06:56.332
{\an8}I just wanted to talk to you
about your test results.

06:56.415 --> 06:58.334
{\an8}Maddy, bring her in.

06:58.417 --> 06:59.335
{\an8}-Can you imagine?
-(laughs)

06:59.418 --> 07:01.129
{\an8}Did she bring Indian food?

07:01.212 --> 07:03.798
{\an8}She have any memes for us?
(laughs)

07:03.881 --> 07:06.134
{\an8}(exhales)
What's wrong with my test?

07:06.217 --> 07:07.677
{\an8}Well, uh, nothing.

07:07.760 --> 07:09.679
{\an8}It-It's-it's actually weird,
you know,

07:09.762 --> 07:11.806
{\an8}because, like,
you technically can't really get

07:11.889 --> 07:13.349
{\an8}lower than five on average...

07:13.432 --> 07:14.475
{\an8}Okay, what the hell
are you talking about?

07:14.559 --> 07:15.768
{\an8}Use your words.

07:16.769 --> 07:19.438
{\an8}You got zero on every test.

07:20.439 --> 07:21.732
{\an8}So?

07:21.816 --> 07:23.317
{\an8}That's not possible.

07:23.401 --> 07:25.528
{\an8}It-It's like you know
what the answer is

07:25.611 --> 07:27.738
{\an8}and are specifically
not choosing it.

07:27.822 --> 07:29.657
{\an8}Or it means
I'm really not psychic.

07:29.740 --> 07:31.367
{\an8}Because it's stupid bullshit.

07:31.450 --> 07:32.368
{\an8}But you can't...

07:32.451 --> 07:34.704
{\an8}I know it's hard
to imagine someone who's normal

07:34.787 --> 07:38.249
{\an8}when you are... like you are.

07:38.332 --> 07:41.586
{\an8}N-No, see,
normal would be five right.

07:41.669 --> 07:43.379
{\an8}I don't want to get ahead
of myself here,

07:43.462 --> 07:46.549
{\an8}but you could have,
like, superpowers.

07:46.632 --> 07:49.552
{\an8}Maybe you're suppressing them.
I don't know, but...

07:49.635 --> 07:54.432
{\an8}if you have psychic abilities,
you could do anything.

08:00.146 --> 08:01.397
{\an8}Like what?

08:01.480 --> 08:03.191
{\an8}I don't know.
Whatever you wanted.

08:03.274 --> 08:05.526
{\an8}Cool stuff.
I-I'd like to do another test.

08:05.610 --> 08:07.737
{\an8}GWEN: Maddy, if you want to go
off with your new friend...

08:07.820 --> 08:10.615
{\an8}ARNA: Don't you know
that being a dork is contagious?

08:11.616 --> 08:13.534
{\an8}Uh, yeah, no, sorry.

08:13.618 --> 08:15.286
{\an8}I don't have
your dumb nerd powers.

08:15.369 --> 08:16.370
{\an8}(girls laughing)

08:16.454 --> 08:18.456
{\an8}Go, Maddy.

08:18.539 --> 08:20.791
{\an8}MADISON: I give her two weeks
till she transfers.

08:20.875 --> 08:22.293
{\an8}(girls laughing)

08:27.340 --> 08:29.675
{\an8}♪ ♪

08:45.816 --> 08:48.486
{\an8}(laughing)

08:50.279 --> 08:52.573
{\an8}♪ ♪

09:08.881 --> 09:11.467
Circle.

09:14.845 --> 09:16.847
Cross.

09:22.353 --> 09:24.689
Star?

09:32.363 --> 09:34.532
This is stupid.

09:36.742 --> 09:38.160
{\an8}Cross.

09:38.244 --> 09:39.704
{\an8}Square.

09:39.787 --> 09:40.830
{\an8}Waves.

09:40.913 --> 09:43.624
{\an8}S-Star.

09:43.708 --> 09:45.293
{\an8}(exhales)

09:45.376 --> 09:47.336
{\an8}Square. Star.

09:47.420 --> 09:49.171
Cross. Circle. Cross.

09:49.255 --> 09:50.506
Star. Cross.

09:50.589 --> 09:52.633
Square, circle, waves.

09:55.594 --> 09:57.388
What the fuck?

10:02.768 --> 10:05.354
(indistinct chatter)

10:27.793 --> 10:29.795
♪ ♪

10:57.448 --> 10:58.741
(gasps)

10:58.824 --> 11:00.284
Thought you could prank me,
bitch?

11:00.368 --> 11:01.869
-What?
-Thought you could scare me

11:01.952 --> 11:03.537
with your stupid cards?

11:03.621 --> 11:04.789
-Tell me the fucking trick!
-I...

11:04.872 --> 11:06.749
I-I swear, Madison,
it's not a trick.

11:06.832 --> 11:09.335
-Bullshit!
-Madison, I swear.

11:11.670 --> 11:14.465
-Do you think I'm stupid?
-No.

11:14.548 --> 11:15.966
What's your little plan?

11:16.050 --> 11:17.635
Th-They're just cards.

11:17.718 --> 11:19.929
They're just cards with pictures
on them, that's it.

11:20.012 --> 11:22.348
Then how come I know
what's on every fucking card?

11:22.431 --> 11:23.891
Because you're special!

11:24.767 --> 11:27.770
You're, like, I-I don't know,
you have psychic powers

11:27.853 --> 11:30.815
or something, which is crazy,
because I didn't even

11:30.898 --> 11:32.775
really think they were real,
okay? Like...

11:32.858 --> 11:34.568
I don't know, okay?
Look, if it's real,

11:34.652 --> 11:37.279
it's, like, the coolest thing
to ever, ever happen

11:37.363 --> 11:38.948
to, like, anyone.

11:39.031 --> 11:40.783
Jesus. Stop talking.

11:55.840 --> 11:57.842
So what do I do?

11:59.552 --> 12:01.637
Uh, I don't know.

12:01.721 --> 12:03.764
I mean, I-I know a lot
about psychic stuff,

12:03.848 --> 12:05.433
but I-I've never actually...

12:05.516 --> 12:07.935
met a real psychic before.

12:09.520 --> 12:11.772
I... I guess we could,
you know...

12:11.856 --> 12:14.316
(chuckles):
or <i> you</i> could...

12:14.400 --> 12:16.652
figure out what powers you have,
and then we could...

12:16.735 --> 12:19.071
figure out how
to use them for stuff?

12:21.532 --> 12:22.825
Fine.

12:26.579 --> 12:30.040
If this is a prank,
I'll ruin your life.

12:30.124 --> 12:31.792
I promise it's not.

12:31.876 --> 12:34.044
(whispers):
Okay.

12:35.045 --> 12:36.630
(door creaks)

12:43.429 --> 12:45.764
<i>("Roads" by Rose of the West</i>
<i>playing)</i>

13:10.956 --> 13:12.708
♪<i> Roads</i> ♪

13:12.791 --> 13:17.046
♪<i> Where do we go,</i>
<i>where do we go?</i> ♪

13:20.132 --> 13:22.676
♪<i> Away from the places we know</i> ♪

13:22.760 --> 13:25.763
♪<i> To somewhere we don't</i> ♪

13:27.139 --> 13:29.433
♪<i> And if we make a wrong turn</i> ♪

13:29.517 --> 13:32.019
♪<i> If we take the long way</i> ♪

13:32.102 --> 13:33.062
♪<i> I swear it's okay</i> ♪

13:33.145 --> 13:35.564
♪<i> Oh...</i> ♪

13:35.648 --> 13:39.443
Okay. Okay, great.

13:39.527 --> 13:41.612
♪<i> Oh</i> ♪

13:41.695 --> 13:45.533
♪<i> Oh.</i> ♪

13:49.787 --> 13:51.080
(scoffs)

13:51.163 --> 13:53.791
What, are you trying
to burn the place down?

13:53.874 --> 13:56.544
Well, I read that, uh,
natural lights and fire

13:56.627 --> 13:59.046
can help with psychic focus.

13:59.129 --> 14:01.131
But, I mean, we could just use
the regular light.

14:01.215 --> 14:02.925
MADISON:
This is so corny.

14:04.510 --> 14:06.470
So, um...

14:06.554 --> 14:09.139
uh, I wrote down
the major abilities.

14:09.223 --> 14:12.059
Uh, the big ones are
astral projection,

14:12.142 --> 14:13.936
clairvoyance, conjuration...

14:14.019 --> 14:15.729
Wait, hang on. Stop.

14:15.813 --> 14:17.898
None of that shit
means anything.

14:17.982 --> 14:21.443
Okay, right. So, there's...

14:21.527 --> 14:23.779
Right. So, this one is
projecting your mind

14:23.862 --> 14:26.657
into another place
so you can see things.

14:26.740 --> 14:29.493
Uh, the next one is
reading people's minds.

14:29.577 --> 14:31.996
Conjuration is the ability
to materialize objects

14:32.079 --> 14:33.581
out of thin air.

14:33.664 --> 14:35.583
Dowsing is sensing
where water is.

14:35.666 --> 14:37.918
Yeah, we don't need to check
for that one.

14:38.002 --> 14:40.129
I don't care where water is.

14:40.212 --> 14:42.006
Right.

14:42.089 --> 14:44.675
(chuckles): Who needs
to know where water is?

14:46.343 --> 14:48.053
Okay.

14:49.054 --> 14:51.181
Okay, then there's, um, flying,

14:51.265 --> 14:54.935
moving stuff, knowing stuff,
seeing the future,

14:55.019 --> 14:56.937
planting thoughts
into people's heads,

14:57.021 --> 14:59.481
and, finally, um,
controlling fire with your mind.

14:59.565 --> 15:00.816
That's a power?

15:00.899 --> 15:02.860
I mean, it's been reported.

15:03.861 --> 15:05.863
That would be cool.

15:07.239 --> 15:10.284
Why do you care
about all this shit?

15:11.285 --> 15:13.120
I don't know.

15:13.203 --> 15:15.581
Don't you want to be normal?

15:16.915 --> 15:18.792
Or cool?

15:18.876 --> 15:20.210
Yeah. I... I mean,

15:20.294 --> 15:22.796
I-I didn't even want to do
this project, you know?

15:22.880 --> 15:25.132
But, like, Ms. Watson made me.

15:25.215 --> 15:30.554
Like, I wanted to do something
about, like, marijuana...

15:30.638 --> 15:33.140
or getting high,
like, how cool that is.

15:33.223 --> 15:34.808
(laughs):
Okay.

15:34.892 --> 15:36.727
So what do we do here?

15:36.810 --> 15:38.312
Test you here.

15:38.395 --> 15:41.649
Uh, see what kinds of powers
you have, and then maybe

15:41.732 --> 15:43.859
we can figure out
how to use them for stuff.

15:45.986 --> 15:47.988
So, uh, what do you see?

15:48.072 --> 15:49.823
Circle.

15:51.408 --> 15:54.244
Yes. Wow.

15:54.328 --> 15:56.163
Wow. Okay. Cool.

15:56.246 --> 15:57.873
Yeah. Wow.

15:57.956 --> 16:00.042
Why don't I know
how I'm doing it?

16:00.125 --> 16:02.044
Have I always been doing it?

16:02.127 --> 16:06.006
Well, um, you don't
really know how you see,

16:06.090 --> 16:07.257
you just... have it.

16:07.341 --> 16:09.218
So it would follow
that a sixth sense

16:09.301 --> 16:10.761
would be the same way.

16:10.844 --> 16:13.013
Like, you can't feel it,
you-you just have it.

16:13.097 --> 16:14.682
Mm-- Right. But, like...

16:14.765 --> 16:16.850
I've never been able to see
what's on a card,

16:16.934 --> 16:19.019
and now it's like it's nothing.

16:19.103 --> 16:21.897
Yeah. Every time you do it,
you get better at it.

16:21.980 --> 16:23.357
Like anything.

16:24.692 --> 16:26.735
Okay, let's try this.

16:35.452 --> 16:37.871
Hey, what are you doing?

16:37.955 --> 16:40.666
Well, I want to see
if you can read minds

16:40.749 --> 16:42.626
since you have
astral projection.

16:42.710 --> 16:46.088
So... now the card
doesn't exist anymore,

16:46.171 --> 16:48.882
so you can't, like,
look at it in space with, like,

16:48.966 --> 16:52.594
psychic eyes--
you can only read my mind.

16:52.678 --> 16:54.722
So, what do you see?

17:01.854 --> 17:04.189
Look at me.

17:11.864 --> 17:13.615
-Star.
-Yes.

17:13.699 --> 17:15.951
(chuckles)

17:16.034 --> 17:17.953
Do another.

17:18.037 --> 17:20.414
<i>("Top of the World" by Kimbra</i>
<i>playing)</i>

